WHAT WAS IMPORTED, AND WHAT WAS DELIBERATELY NOT
------------------------------------------------

This repository is NOT a fork of the CairnMap tree. It is a fresh repository
that imports only the subset of that tree which Pixnop authored and can
therefore license under MIT:

    cpp-mod/          the UE4SS C++ mod        (47/47 commits by Pixnop)
    tools/codegen/    data -> header codegen   (authored by Pixnop)
    tools/extract-locations/  offline pak extraction tooling
    tools/runtime-fix/        Lua compat shim for the legacy 5.1 pak
    docs/             design docs / specs
    .github/          CI
    data/locations/   coordinate data, relocated from
                      Content/Mods/MapCollectablesMod/Data/

The upstream repository is a GitHub fork of miapuffia/MapCollectablesMod and
so carries three distinct provenances under one MIT file. The following were
NOT imported, because Pixnop cannot license them and they are not needed to
build the mod:

    Content/      miapuffia's upstream tree -- that repository has NO license
    Source/       PalworldModdingKit (Pocketpair)
    Plugins/      PalworldModdingKit (48 plugins incl. Wwise, DLSS, FSR2)
    Config/       PalworldModdingKit
    Pal.uproject  PalworldModdingKit

This is why GitHub reports the upstream repository's license as NOASSERTION
despite the MIT LICENSE file. Importing only the MIT-clean subset is what
makes this repository's license story unambiguous.


PROVENANCE OF data/locations/*.json
-----------------------------------

These files were relocated out of Content/ but are Pixnop's work, not
miapuffia's, and are therefore MIT-covered. Verified against upstream git
history:

  - All 24 files were authored or regenerated by Pixnop on 2026-07-12/13
    ("Regenerate all location data from 1.0 world files; add offline
    extraction tooling", then "Filter location data to surface nodes
    (z > -15000)").
  - EffigyLocations.json and NoteLocations.json were created fresh by Pixnop
    on 2026-07-12; they are not miapuffia's hand-tracked data.
  - CoalLocations.json is the only file whose history reaches back to
    miapuffia (v5.0.0, 2025-01-21), but its current content was fully
    regenerated by Pixnop from the 1.0 world files.

The coordinates themselves are facts datamined from Palworld's own cooked
level data. They are not sourced from any third-party website. In particular,
no data was taken from palworld.gg, palworld.th.gl, or any other community
map site.


